# Windsurf Coding Standards for Project Sheng V1

## Code Quality Standards
- **Type Hinting**: All functions must have complete type annotations
- **PEP 8 Compliance**: Strict adherence to Python style guidelines
- **Docstrings**: Google-style docstrings for all public functions
- **Error Handling**: Explicit exception handling with custom exceptions

## Project Structure
```
sheng_sentiment_base/
├── src/
│   ├── scrapers/          # Data collection modules
│   ├── tokenizers/        # NLP preprocessing
│   ├── pipelines/         # Data processing workflows
│   └── utils/             # Helper utilities
├── data/
│   ├── raw/               # Unprocessed scraped data
│   ├── processed/         # Cleaned datasets
│   └── dictionaries/        # Sheng slang mappings
├── tests/                 # Unit and integration tests
├── docs/                  # Documentation
└── notebooks/             # Exploration notebooks
```

## Git Conventions
- Format: `type(scope): description`
- Types: feat, fix, docs, test, refactor, perf
- Example: `feat(scraper): add rate-limited X API client`

## Naming Conventions
- Classes: PascalCase (e.g., `ShengTokenizer`)
- Functions: snake_case (e.g., `normalize_slang`)
- Constants: UPPER_SNAKE_CASE
- Private: _leading_underscore
